{
  "local_port": 46616,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm sick of hearing about Trump, can I block these questions on my Quora feed?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you're feeling overwhelmed by Trump-related content on your Quora feed. Fortunately, Quora offers several ways to customize your experience and reduce the appearance of topics you're not interested in. Here's how you can manage and filter out Trump-related questions:\n\n### 1. **Unfollow Relevant Topics**\nQuora organizes content based on topics you follow. By unfollowing topics related to Donald Trump, you can significantly reduce related content in your feed.\n\n- **Steps to Unfollow Topics:**\n  1. **Navigate to Your Feed:**\n     - Go to [Quora's homepage](https://www.quora.com/) and ensure you're logged in.\n  2. **Access Your Topics:**\n     - On the left sidebar (desktop) or tap your profile picture and navigate to \"Topics\" (mobile), you'll see a list of topics you're following.\n  3. **Find and Unfollow Trump-Related Topics:**\n     - Look for topics like \"Donald Trump,\" \"US Politics,\" or any other related subjects.\n     - Click the `Following` button next to the topic to unfollow it.\n\n### 2. **Hide Specific Questions**\nIf you come across a Trump-related question in your feed, you can hide it. Over time, Quora's algorithm will learn your preferences and show less similar content.\n\n- **How to Hide a Question:**\n  1. **Locate the Question:**\n     - Find the Trump-related question in your feed.\n  2. **Hide It:**\n     - Click on the three-dot menu (`\u22ef`) located at the top-right corner of the question.\n     - Select **\"Hide Question\"** from the dropdown menu.\n\n### 3. **Block Specific Users**\nIf certain users frequently post about Trump, you can block them to prevent their content from appearing in your feed.\n\n- **Steps to Block a User:**\n  1. **Visit the User's Profile:**\n     - Click on the user's name to go to their profile page.\n  2. **Block the User:**\n     - Click the three-dot menu (`\u22ef`) on their profile.\n     - Select **\"Block\"** from the options.\n     - Confirm the action when prompted.\n\n### 4. **Adjust Your Interests**\nRegularly reviewing and updating your interests ensures that your feed aligns with your current preferences.\n\n- **How to Update Interests:**\n  1. **Go to Your Profile:**\n     - Click on your profile picture and select **\"Settings\"**.\n  2. **Edit Interests:**\n     - Under the **\"Interests\"** section, add topics you\u2019re passionate about and remove or unfollow those you\u2019re not.\n  3. **Save Changes:**\n     - Ensure you save any changes to update your feed preferences.\n\n### 5. **Use the \"Not Interested\" Feature**\nQuora allows you to mark certain content as \"Not Interested,\" helping to refine what appears in your feed.\n\n- **How to Use It:**\n  1. **Find the Content:**\n     - When you see a Trump-related question or answer, click on the three-dot menu (`\u22ef`).\n  2. **Mark as Not Interested:**\n     - Select **\"Not Interested\"** to help Quora tailor your feed accordingly.\n\n### 6. **Provide Feedback to Quora**\nLetting Quora know about your preferences can aid in improving your content recommendations.\n\n- **How to Submit Feedback:**\n  1. **Scroll to the Bottom:**\n     - On any Quora page, scroll down to the footer.\n  2. **Click on \"Feedback\":**\n     - Provide detailed feedback about the type of content you wish to see less of.\n\n### 7. **Utilize Browser Extensions for Enhanced Filtering**\nIf Quora's built-in features aren't sufficient, you can use browser extensions to block or filter unwanted content based on keywords.\n\n- **Recommended Extensions:**\n  - **Personal Blocklist (by Google):** Allows you to block specific keywords from appearing on websites.\n  - **uBlock Origin:** A versatile ad blocker that can be customized to hide specific elements based on keywords.\n\n- **How to Set Up:**\n  1. **Install the Extension:**\n     - Visit your browser's extension store and install the preferred tool.\n  2. **Configure Keyword Filters:**\n     - Add keywords like \"Trump,\" \"Donald Trump,\" etc., to the blocklist.\n  3. **Refresh Quora:**\n     - Reload your Quora feed to see the changes take effect.\n\n### 8. **Regularly Review Your Feed and Adjust Settings**\nContent algorithms learn over time. Periodically review your feed and adjust your settings to ensure the platform continues to meet your preferences.\n\n- **Tips:**\n  - Regularly hide or mark content as \"Not Interested.\"\n  - Update your followed topics based on evolving interests.\n  - Engage with content you enjoy to help Quora better understand your preferences.\n\n### 9. **Reach Out to Quora Support**\nIf you've tried the above methods and still encounter excessive Trump-related content, consider contacting Quora's support team for personalized assistance.\n\n- **How to Contact Support:**\n  1. **Visit the Help Center:**\n     - Go to [Quora Help](https://help.quora.com/) for resources and contact options.\n  2. **Submit a Request:**\n     - Use the provided forms to detail your issue and seek further guidance.\n\n---\n\nBy implementing these strategies, you should experience a more tailored and enjoyable Quora feed that aligns with your interests. Remember that it might take some time for the changes to fully reflect as the platform's algorithms adapt to your new preferences.\n\nIf you have any other questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!",
